  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving mine action assistance to IDPs and host communities in the Boucle du Mouhoun, Centre-Nord, Est, Nord, and Sahel regions. This UNOPS project, on behalf of UNMAS, helps prevent life-altering and life-threatening accidents by raising awareness about the risks of improvised explosive devices. The project provides life-saving assistance to 50,000 people, including 10,660 women and 29,500 children.</narrative>
  </description>
